lltrades>Anien Alltrades</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 3:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1180.topic>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Mages and the Shaman Epic Rak fight</span><hr size=1> I can't seem to find the posts I read about what I should do to get the fire pet to resist his AE, could someone point me to it?  Whatever I attempted last night didn't work too well, but being the only mage prolly didn't help either.<br>
Thanks in advance!<br>
Anien Altrades<br>
lvl 57 Mage<br>
Prexus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thoorne>thoorne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 4:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1180.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   wuwu</span><hr size=1> I did it duoing with a shammy...<br>
Took something like 25 minutes.<br>
<br>
49th fire pet tanked him. He died slowly. Pet was immune to AE. And this was AFTER the resists changes on pets. But my pet took 0 dmg from AE, and I had quite low FR (around 80). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nucci01>Nucci 01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 148<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 4:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1180.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wuwu</span><hr size=1> - Use your 57 earth pet or epic if you have it<br>
- cast elemental armor on yourself<br>
- wear an elemental blanket on your shoulders<br>
- have the shaman make a fire resistance potion<br>
- cast cadeau of flame on yourself<br>
<br>
This should easily get you to around 200ish or higher fire resist which should be fine.<br>
<br>
BTW, any player that can get their SVFire over 200 is safe to engage Rak, this is no longer a &quot;mage only&quot; encounter.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=465781">Master Nucci</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=569788">Angborr<br>
</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=axxin>Axxin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 4:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1180.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wuwu</span><hr size=1> That's the trick.  Make sure your own FR is low enough that your pet will use his own. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=devictionmt>DevictionMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 217<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 4:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1180.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wuwu</span><hr size=1> Whats so tricky about that?  If your FR is higher than the fire pet, then use it.<br>
<br>
 <p>Deviction Xue <br>
lvl 56 Mage<br>
MT<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pissed1vi2soe@themagicianstower>Pissed1VI2SOE</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 614<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 4:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1180.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   wuuu</span><hr size=1> If your FR can be gotten over 200, you'll be safe but your Fire pet will lose it's natural Immunity, so your better off using a different pet.<br>
<br>
If your FR is under 200, then DROP it below 100 and use 49 Fire pet.<br>
<br>
--Or--<br>
<br>
Just use a tank, had a 60 warrior with FR over 200 solo tank him w/o a problem.  Sure we lost a few wizzards, because they weren't  smart enough to move out of AoE range.  2-3 healers should suffice, he drops fast with a real tank and a pet or 2 on him.<br>
<br>
Did him again w/ everyone having around 150ish FR, noone died, 6 person group 60's and up, was a laughable encounter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ithryn>Ithryn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 170<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 4:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1180.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wuuu</span><hr size=1> I tried it about 3 weeks ago and my lvl 49 fire pet got nuked to oblivion every 20 seconds or so.<br>
<br>
This is with my fire resist at below 40 to start the fight, then I debuffed myself to -5 (yes, negative 5) during the fight.<br>
<br>
Every pet died to the AE, even after we sent in a tank to engage Rak.<br>
<br>
With the new levels, spells, aa abilities, and equipment that SoL and PoP have introduced, you really don't need to resort to any tricks to beat Rak.  Send in a good tank and keep a cleric back out of his ae range to heal the tank.  Maybe ahve another healer for fast spot heals if necessary. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=anienalltrades>Anien Alltrades</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 5:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1180.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wuuu</span><hr size=1> Thanks guys, had I known, I would have gone for the 200+, since I can do that self buffed, no potion needed.<br>
Anien Altrades<br>
lvl 57 Mage<br>
Prexus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yizanpetpimpin>Yizan Pet Pimpin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 8:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1180.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home1.gte.net/res0rg9w/tomoanim3.gif width=100 height=125></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wuuu</span><hr size=1> I did this earlier this week.  I simply got out the 61 Air pet, got him cleric buffed, and put Flameshield of Ro on him.  Then I broke out all my fire resist gear, Diamond/Blue Diamond gear, summoned mantle, couple other trinkets, put the 61 Elemental armor on myself and a Flameshield of Ro, all this put my fire resist just over 270, sent pet in, cleric healed him, me and shaman sat and watched the show.  Took less that 5 minutes, shaman looted up and we all gated back to PoK.  With PoP spells and pet this encounter is nearly trival anymore. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
