<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Destruction is an art.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nirrudn@themagicianstower>Nirrudn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 218<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 9:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1180.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wuuu</span><hr size=1> Did Rak shortly after PoP came out, and we used a 61 warrior to tank.<br>
<br>
He said with 70FR, the AE never even hit him once.  Perhaps it's limited by level? <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/nirrudnsok/sig.txt" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/nirrudnsok/crit.txt" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krilenspiritlink>Krilen Spiritlink</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 709<br> <font color=#333333>(2/20/03 6:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1180.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wuuu</span><hr size=1> The reason the warrior never got hit once with the AE is probably because the mob dies in 3 seconds. <p>Happy trails.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=celanxev>CelanXev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 270<br> <font color=#333333>(2/20/03 12:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1180.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re:</span><hr size=1> Cool, so you duoed him with a shammy? And used air and did him with shammy + cleric? That's good news. I am now 2boxing a shammy and will eventually want to do the epic. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zeem@themagicianstower>Zeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 555<br> <font color=#333333>(2/20/03 2:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1180.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   FlameSongOfRo</span><hr size=1> This spell have a -100 resist adjust, basicly ... don't count of going a full fight against him and resist it all the time.<br>
<br>
I want my pet to get back thier immunity to certain spells again  :-(. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=booperbustle>Booperbustle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#333333>(2/20/03 3:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1180.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: FlameSongOfRo</span><hr size=1> Honestly, I think they removed or severely nerfed the AE.  Before PoP I remember seeing the message &quot;Your pet's FlameshieldofRo spell has worn off&quot;.  When I do the Rak fight these days I use either epic or Ward of Xegony.  Just given pet gear and a few hp buffs both were able to tank Rak with only me and another healer backing him up.  Another mage used 49 fire and/or Dyzil's Deafening Decoy, both getting mauled by Rak (have done this fight about 5 or so times since PoP came out).  The AE &quot;worn off&quot; message never did pop up though, so I'm guessing they removed the AE or it is broken.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=222062">Booperbustle Tinkermeister</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Arch Convoker of Solusek Ro and Grand Master Tinkerer (230)<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub15.ezboard.com/bfuriouspantaloons">Furious Pantaloons</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jarlo99>Jarlo99</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#333333>(2/20/03 10:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1180.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: FlameSongOfRo</span><hr size=1> I always thought the pet's resists were set to yours at the time of summoning.  Do the pets resists change AFTER summon if you change yours?<br>
 <p>Jarly Neverwinter lvl 42 Human Enchantress<br>
<br>
Jarlork Firestorm<br>
